 Local LLM for clinical NLP: Phi-3-mini or Llama 3.2 3B (quantized, GGUF format via llama.cpp)
 Task: extract medications, dosages, diagnoses, allergies, procedures from free text → FHIR resources
 All AI suggestions presented with confidence score; low-confidence items go to review queue
 No patient data ever sent to an external API without explicit consent and institutional approval — this is a hard architectural constraint

Model Management

 Model registry: each deployment declares which models it has locally
 Models distributed as signed packages through the app update system (not patient data channels)
 A/B testing framework for model versions at T3+ (hospital can evaluate new models before deploying)


