The Error Scenario: 1mg vs 1g Cefazolin
Setting
Post-induction, Sr. Kavitha is recording antibiotic prophylaxis administration. In the rush, she enters 1mg cefazolin instead of 1g.
Tier 1: Heuristic Flagging — Immediate, On-Device
This happens before the record is committed, at the UI validation layer and in the Rust core:
Input received:
  { drug: "Cefazolin", dose: 1, unit: "mg", route: "IV", 
    context: "surgical prophylaxis" }

Rust Core — Clinical Rules Engine:
  Rule set loaded: drug_dosage_heuristics.json
  (local file, updated with app, no internet needed)
  
  Rule fired:
    drug: "Cefazolin"
    indication_context: "surgical prophylaxis"
    expected_dose_range: { min: 500mg, max: 2000mg, typical: 1000mg }
    entered_dose: 1mg
    
  Heuristic result:
    SEVERITY: HIGH
    FLAG: DOSE_BELOW_MINIMUM_THERAPEUTIC
    message: "Entered dose (1mg) is 1000× below minimum 
              therapeutic dose for surgical prophylaxis (500mg).
              Did you mean 1g (1000mg)?"
    
  Magnitude check (catches unit errors specifically):
    ratio = expected_typical / entered = 1000mg / 1mg = 1000
    ratio > 100 → trigger UNIT_ERROR_SUSPECTED flag
    suggestion: "Check unit — possible mg/g confusion"

UI Response:
  Modal alert (cannot be dismissed by tapping outside):
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  ⚠ DOSE VERIFICATION REQUIRED      │
  │                                     │
  │  Cefazolin 1mg IV                   │
  │  This is 1000× below the expected   │
  │  prophylactic dose.                 │
  │                                     │
  │  Did you mean: 1g (1000mg)?         │
  │                                     │
  │  [Correct to 1g]  [Enter manually]  │
  │  [Override with reason]             │
  └─────────────────────────────────────┘
  
  "Enter manually" requires re-entry from scratch (not just confirm)
  "Override with reason" requires text entry + identity re-auth (PIN)
The ideal path ends here — Kavitha taps "Correct to 1g", the right dose is entered, record committed cleanly.

Tier 2: If Entered Into the Record Anyway
Suppose Kavitha is flustered, the surgeon is asking, and she taps "Override" without reading carefully, entering a reason of "confirmed" and re-auths with her PIN. The record is now committed with Cefazolin 1mg.
